The paper discusses the implementation and analysis of a data structure, specifically a non-blocking concurrent interpolation search tree (C-IST). This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of the C-IST in a concurrent setting, which could fall under the categories of programming languages (cs.PL), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), performance (cs.PF), and systems and control (cs.SY).
